Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.14,0:00:03.48,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.91,0:00:07.44,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I believe Executioners \Ntypically operate in pairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.44,0:00:11.40,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Given that his partner hasn't appeared, \Nhe doesn't seem to be lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.94,0:00:15.87,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Make them hurt so bad that \Nthey wish they'd never been born.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.40,0:00:17.83,Default,Matt,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.79,0:00:24.04,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,You'll look out for me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.48,0:00:26.15,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.15,0:00:29.50,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,We can guard you like a precious gem.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.04,0:00:38.79,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,But we'd also welcome your help, \Nif you should feel so inclined.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:17.40,Default,Text,0,0,0,,{\blur0.3\fs18\bord0.5\shad1\fnTimes New Roman\fscx90\fad(0,400)\1c&H000000&\3c&H000000&\4c&H000000&\t(0,500,\3c&H17282F&\c&HF8EBE4&\4c&H818486&)\t(3940,3941,\3c&H4D4732&)\pos(81,314)}Origin Witch
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:21.45,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.45,0:02:22.37,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.37,0:02:27.62,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,I missed my chance to ask earlier, \Nbut did I have my precious first kiss with...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.47,0:02:37.18,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.71,0:02:39.52,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Was there always a door here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.52,0:02:42.03,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,No. Not until just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.47,0:02:44.92,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,But never mind that. You were saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.92,0:02:48.06,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Never mind. I'd rather not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.62,0:02:55.20,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,So what is this place? The infamous \NOrder of Magical Resonance's HQ?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.20,0:02:57.99,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,No way, right? It's way too small.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.20,0:03:00.24,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,You're right. It isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.24,0:03:03.21,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,For starters, we don't have a headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.21,0:03:05.91,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,At least, not one that anyone knows about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.91,0:03:08.13,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,This is an entrance to the Corridors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.64,0:03:14.31,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Helga, this route is just for us, \Nso that I can escort you safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.00,0:03:16.20,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.34,0:03:19.51,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.51,0:03:21.93,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Be good and wait here, Guideau.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.28,0:03:26.93,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Patch me up. Moving like \Nthis is a pain in the ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.93,0:03:28.35,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,You'll only be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.82,0:03:30.94,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Why do you need to move?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.20,0:03:42.24,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Are you sure about leaving her behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.24,0:03:45.97,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Yes. The Order demands \Nconfidentiality on several points.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.97,0:03:50.33,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I know you agreed to a magical \Ncontract to keep our secrets,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:52.19,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,but Guideau refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.19,0:03:54.92,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,As such, the Order's inner \Nworkings remain off-limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.92,0:03:57.25,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,All the more reason not to risk leaving her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.60,0:04:00.52,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,I can't see her sitting tight \Nand staying out of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.52,0:04:01.81,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.81,0:04:05.89,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Following the mission and my orders is the shortest path to Guideau's goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.89,0:04:08.22,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,and Guideau knows it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.48,0:04:09.73,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.73,0:04:12.38,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,My partner is more rational \Nthan you might think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.38,0:04:14.69,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,We shouldn't need to worry \Nabout pointless mischief.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.60,0:04:20.14,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Then again, Guideau has been known \Nto act on instinct despite knowing better.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.52,0:04:23.53,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,A few exceptions fall into that category,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.53,0:04:28.68,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,but I hardly expect one to turn up\N in a country town like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:32.91,Default,Boy 1,0,0,0,,A witch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.20,0:04:35.22,Default,Boy 2,0,0,0,,I saw her! I saw her! A witch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:36.37,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.75,0:04:40.38,Default,Boy 1,0,0,0,,Yeah! I saw her brewing some kinda potion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.38,0:04:43.34,Default,Boy 2,0,0,0,,She's really there! \NA witch with a big cauldron!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.34,0:04:46.14,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,She's brewing up poisons to curse people!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.14,0:04:49.42,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,See? What did I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.42,0:04:51.20,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,And you didn't believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.20,0:04:52.89,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,Yeah. That was our bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.36,0:04:55.26,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,So what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.26,0:04:57.79,Default,Boy 1,0,0,0,,The grown-ups won't \Nbelieve us if we tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.79,0:04:59.77,Default,Boy 2,0,0,0,,We'll have to get her ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.77,0:05:00.56,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.56,0:05:01.48,Default,Boy 1; 2; Angela,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.25,0:05:04.72,Default,Boy 1,0,0,0,,Did you hear something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.42,0:05:06.57,Default,Boy 2,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:11.92,Default,Boy 1,0,0,0,,Wh-What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.92,0:05:12.87,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.87,0:05:13.75,Default,Boy 2,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.40,0:05:17.75,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Where's the witch? Take me to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.05,0:05:19.88,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,What?! Where'd you come from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:21.00,Default,Boy 1,0,0,0,,You're not making sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.63,0:05:26.91,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,What a pain. I'll kill you one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.91,0:05:29.51,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Make up your minds before \Nthere's only one of you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.94,0:05:34.85,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,W-We'll do it. We'll take you to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.61,0:05:50.66,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,Uh, this is the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.43,0:06:00.33,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,Huh? Y-You're going in? It's not safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.48,0:06:13.64,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Oh? What charming little visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.88,0:06:20.90,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Oh, goodness gracious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.64,0:06:22.56,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.85,0:06:24.53,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,It won't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:28.65,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Your leg froze up? That's serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.65,0:06:30.98,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,I'd better put it right for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:38.30,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Hey! What's your problem?!\N Get out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.47,0:06:41.58,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Now my left arm's busted, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.58,0:06:43.60,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Hey, now. Stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.60,0:06:45.65,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Injured people need care.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.38,0:06:51.76,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,No need to act so skittish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.76,0:06:55.60,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Customers love this ointment. \NIt's my secret recipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.60,0:06:57.10,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Dear me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.15,0:07:00.78,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,You certainly heal quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.32,0:07:02.98,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,This smell...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.98,0:07:06.78,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,You're not a witch, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.30,0:07:15.45,Default,Receptionist,0,0,0,,Welcome back. \NWill you be using the Corridors?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.74,0:07:18.08,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Yes, I'd like to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:20.16,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Where do these connect to?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.16,0:07:26.30,Default,Receptionist,0,0,0,,We're in contact with \Nrooms 5010, 6288, and 7006.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.77,0:07:29.15,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,And room 7006 would be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.15,0:07:31.01,Default,Receptionist,0,0,0,,On the Sixth Continent, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.25,0:07:33.27,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Yes, that will do nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.62,0:07:37.86,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,I have no clue what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.86,0:07:40.14,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,This will make sense to me one day, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.14,0:07:44.50,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Of course. And unlike Guideau, \NI'm happy to say you'll be worth teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:48.82,Default,Receptionist,0,0,0,,Mr. Ashaf, this just arrived for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.98,0:07:50.78,Italics,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Black...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.32,0:07:56.20,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.01,0:08:00.97,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Wait here for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.97,0:08:01.66,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.21,0:08:02.92,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.69,0:08:04.78,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.99,0:08:12.55,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Now, listen here. I do use magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.55,0:08:15.84,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,but I'm still only a humble herbalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:20.68,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Calling me a witch is an insult to witches.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:21.81,Default,Boy 2,0,0,0,,We're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.09,0:08:24.38,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,This is so heavy. Hold it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.38,0:08:25.90,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,Do your fair share.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.32,0:08:30.32,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,Your silly stories got us \Ninto this mess, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.26,0:08:35.28,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.10,0:08:40.95,Default,Old Woman,0,0,0,,My, my. So many visitors today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.95,0:08:43.91,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Hey, where the hell did you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.30,0:08:47.13,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,I didn't sense you till the door opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.47,0:08:48.34,Default,Boy 3,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.16,0:08:55.14,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:08:57.36,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,an Executioner!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.92,0:09:18.06,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,You must be wondering where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.22,0:09:22.52,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,This is my private world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.23,0:09:26.86,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,An alternate dimension reached \Nby passing inside this cloak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.83,0:09:32.67,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,You can't even perceive it \Nunless you have the cloak on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.26,0:09:37.76,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,Your senses don't function.\N I doubt you can even think clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.37,0:09:40.44,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,But you're special.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.36,0:09:43.75,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,I'll allow you a bit of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.21,0:09:47.08,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,I have questions for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.91,0:09:53.83,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,Executioners work in pairs.\N I have a partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.36,0:09:59.74,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,He started acting strangely, \Nso I followed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.74,0:10:02.10,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,But I suppose I caught on too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.61,0:10:06.25,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,By the time I arrived, \Neverything seemed to be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.71,0:10:11.60,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,You stayed at the scene, so I shadowed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.60,0:10:12.84,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,But what a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.86,0:10:17.94,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,I could never have managed it \Nwithout this Forbidden Instrument,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.94,0:10:20.10,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,which lets me vanish from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.96,0:10:23.56,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,The Order of Magical Resonance \Nlives up to its reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.72,0:10:29.44,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,Now you see where you stand.\N On to business.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.76,0:10:32.94,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,I have two questions for you,\N both quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.24,0:10:38.07,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,Where is my little brother \Nand his Forbidden Instrument?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.57,0:10:45.58,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Hey, are you done now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.40,0:10:50.42,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,I'd like to chat with this little one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.46,0:10:59.46,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Ashaf!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.73,0:11:00.68,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Ashaf!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.99,0:11:04.14,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,What happened? What could\Nhave rattled you this badly?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.56,0:11:07.10,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm rattled, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.41,0:11:09.74,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,There's a witch in this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.55,0:11:12.77,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,And not just any witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.44,0:11:16.19,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,The "hateful witch" who cursed Guideau.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.34,0:11:18.81,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Her name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.25,0:11:29.42,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Angela!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.80,0:11:40.47,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,You bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.67,0:11:44.10,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.10,0:11:45.39,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,I've missed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.92,0:11:49.02,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,Since this space isn't affecting you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.36,0:11:52.45,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,that cloak must be more \Nthan a fashion statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.45,0:11:55.36,Default,Executioner,0,0,0,,I thought mine was one of a kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.81,0:11:58.82,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Oh, this? I made one just like yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.00,0:12:02.03,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Nice, right? It comes in handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.03,0:12:04.25,Italics,Executioner,0,0,0,,Does she mean she copied it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.25,0:12:07.74,Italics,Executioner,0,0,0,,This is no mere magical bauble.\N It's a Forbidden Instrument!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.74,0:12:12.83,Italics,Executioner,0,0,0,,And she recreated it, \Nfunction and all, just by looking at it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.00,0:12:18.27,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,But the ones I make wear out in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.25,0:12:21.72,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,So, if you wouldn't mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.03,0:12:23.68,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,give me yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.06,0:12:34.90,Italics,Executioner,0,0,0,,Impossible! How is she standing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.69,0:12:40.34,Italics,Executioner,0,0,0,,I only granted this woman \Nminimal sight and hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.34,0:12:43.28,Italics,Executioner,0,0,0,,She's been deprived\N of all her other senses!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.85,0:12:45.51,Italics,Executioner,0,0,0,,So how?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:48.07,Italics,Executioner,0,0,0,,They're both freaks!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.30,0:12:53.60,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Can you get in touch?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.60,0:12:58.25,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,No, unfortunately. What rotten timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.55,0:13:02.27,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,But even if I could, it wouldn't help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.27,0:13:04.72,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,It's too late for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:08.30,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,The thread is already pulling.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.64,0:13:11.01,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,What? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.31,0:13:14.68,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,A force that pulls people together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.52,0:13:21.57,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,The cursed and the curser \Ndevelop a special type of bond.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.57,0:13:25.90,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Those threads of fate \Ndraw them to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.18,0:13:29.10,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,We call that the threads' pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.10,0:13:34.50,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,While their power is in play, \NI won't find it so easy to intervene.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.54,0:13:37.71,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,In any case, this doesn't look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.08,0:13:42.74,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,When I healed Guideau's body,\N I left it fragile in places, just in case,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.74,0:13:44.67,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,so the kid couldn't cause any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.67,0:13:50.14,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Of course, even in perfect health, \NGuideau wouldn't stand a chance against her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.47,0:13:53.10,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,But in this condition, \Neven escape will prove difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.10,0:13:56.81,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Not that Guideau would ever \Ntry to run from her in any case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.81,0:13:58.69,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,H-Hang on! Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.40,0:14:07.81,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I'm quite calm. I sent out crows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.81,0:14:09.82,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Flailing blindly will get us nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.31,0:14:12.92,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Regardless, you should go back inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.92,0:14:15.00,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Why? I'll help you look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:17.76,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I've been entrusted with your safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.76,0:14:21.30,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,And this is Guideau's problem. \NI can't drag you into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.00,0:14:25.42,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,But I owe you two for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.42,0:14:28.47,Flashback,Guideau,0,0,0,,I've gotta take you with me,\N or I've wasted my time!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.36,0:14:31.39,Flashback,Helga,0,0,0,,Then rescue me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.24,0:14:36.64,Flashback,Helga,0,0,0,,If bringing me back is your job,\N keep the Demon Sword safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.89,0:14:39.11,Flashback,Helga,0,0,0,,Come back and rescue me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.72,0:14:42.59,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,So just this once,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.59,0:14:44.98,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Guideau's problem is my problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.67,0:14:48.36,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,She means a lot to you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.28,0:14:53.66,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Yes, a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.64,0:14:56.85,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Far more than my own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.77,0:15:06.14,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Funny, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.93,0:15:12.59,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,I wanted to see you, \Nbut not that guy who's always with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.03,0:15:15.14,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,So I hid in this town,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.14,0:15:19.31,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,and spread rumors the Church, the Order, \Nand the townsfolk would brush off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:24.61,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Rumors only you would \Ntake seriously, Guideau.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.98,0:15:27.65,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Just a few tall tales.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.15,0:15:31.82,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,And look how perfectly that little \Nbit of scheming worked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.09,0:15:36.16,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,We can see each other anytime, \Nas long as we both feel like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.16,0:15:38.32,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Fate's handy that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:41.37,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,So, Guideau...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.79,0:15:44.45,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,How does it feel, using my body?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.49,0:15:48.63,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,A witch's flesh is all about adaptability,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.63,0:15:54.22,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,so I bet it adjusted to your soul \Nand made things a lot easier for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.40,0:15:58.68,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Hands off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.20,0:16:03.44,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,You don't like being touched? Even though \Nyou have no problem throwing punches?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.61,0:16:05.89,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Talk about picky.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.22,0:16:29.06,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,You look so upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.84,0:16:31.39,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Do you hate me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.59,0:16:36.71,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,You know, I was playing with \Nsomeone else until recently,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.71,0:16:38.29,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,but maybe I got bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.79,0:16:41.38,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,It just wasn't much fun anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.43,0:16:43.60,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Tell me, Guideau...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.07,0:16:47.56,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Is it about time we went at it for real?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.87,0:16:57.60,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,That was a close one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.60,0:16:59.70,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,You were going for a kiss, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.02,0:17:03.02,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Wow. So you know about that trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.55,0:17:04.54,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,But no.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.96,0:17:08.45,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,If you really want to undo \Nmy curse, that isn't the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.45,0:17:09.81,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,and this isn't the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.03,0:17:13.56,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Chase me, Guideau.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.03,0:17:15.90,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,I'll give you signposts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.45,0:17:19.04,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,If you reach them all and catch up to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.04,0:17:21.31,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,I'll live up to your expectations, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.67,0:17:25.98,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,I forget how many decades it's been, \Nbut let's pick up where we left off that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.20,0:17:32.06,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,The Order must have caught on by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.57,0:17:35.70,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,Oh, right. They can't \Nfind me while I have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.08,0:17:37.78,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,What a lucky find.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.81,0:17:43.75,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,I mean, seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.27,0:17:46.48,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,You just never break, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.64,0:17:50.09,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,I swear, Angela...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.69,0:17:54.87,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,I'll kill you if it's the last thing I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.50,0:17:57.98,Default,Angela,0,0,0,,I like that look in your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.05,0:18:11.85,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Guideau!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.00,0:18:16.98,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Still breathing. Nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.98,0:18:19.78,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,You call that "nothing"? \NShe's hanging on by a thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.78,0:18:22.79,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,As long as Guideau's breathing, \Nthe rest works itself out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.37,0:18:24.33,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Hey, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.17,0:18:30.65,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,An Executioner!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.13,0:18:33.92,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,We weren't gone long, \Nand I don't see any sign of a struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.21,0:18:35.17,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Angela...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.67,0:18:38.13,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Who in the world is that witch?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.78,0:18:42.54,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,A celebrity. You've heard of her, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.92,0:18:47.89,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Angela the Origin Witch. \NThat should be all you need to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.17,0:18:49.51,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.51,0:18:51.56,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,You mean {\i1}the{\i0} Angela?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.87,0:18:54.73,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,That can't be right! \NThere's no way she could still be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.27,0:18:58.40,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,Witches are destined to \Nonly live for 200 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.89,0:19:00.78,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Oh, she's alive, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.84,0:19:05.12,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,The "Eternal Witch," Angela Anne Huell,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.70,0:19:08.40,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,one of the world's most powerful witches,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.40,0:19:11.83,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,continues to live on in it to this very day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:17.02,Default,Helga,0,0,0,,If that's true, Guideau chose one \Nhell of a person to pick a fight with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.02,0:19:18.60,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,You said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.65,0:19:25.14,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I suppose it was Angela \Nwho carved those letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.78,0:19:26.47,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.51,0:19:30.14,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,So it begins at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.51,0:19:41.53,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Guideau, are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.46,0:19:44.50,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.01,0:19:53.67,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Did you find her?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.67,0:19:56.37,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,No, can't say I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.37,0:19:57.71,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Then get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.18,0:20:00.82,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Why won't you touch your food?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.82,0:20:02.91,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Just look at you, still covered in wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.36,0:20:08.14,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,You eat and you heal, remember? \NHow could you starve yourself all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.68,0:20:11.47,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,If you won't eat, at least let me treat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.47,0:20:12.60,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Give me a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.49,0:20:16.06,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,What kind of crap are \Nyou gonna pull this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.04,0:20:21.90,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Back there, my arm and leg gave out on me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.32,0:20:29.26,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,because you did something \Nto them, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.74,0:20:31.04,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Stop, Guideau.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.64,0:20:48.79,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,You seem full of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.20,0:20:51.85,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I guess you won't need healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:54.81,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,You won't get another chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.36,0:20:58.88,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Try it again, and I won't wait \Nto undo the curse to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.41,0:21:01.15,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.15,0:21:06.16,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,But I had no intention \Nof setting you up to fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.50,0:21:10.58,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I'm doing my best to \Nassure things go smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:16.17,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Nothing I do is pointless, and I won't \Ndo anything against your interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.58,0:21:18.88,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,You're a valuable human resource.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.88,0:21:23.97,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I would never do anything \Nthat might result in losing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.31,0:21:28.69,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,You understand that our interests align.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.69,0:21:32.10,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,That's why you've obeyed my orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.58,0:21:36.06,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,When you suspect I'm "pulling \Nsomething" in spite of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.41,0:21:39.75,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I'm only doing so for the sake\N of the larger picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.44,0:21:42.44,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Let me repeat myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.44,0:21:47.63,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I'm not your enemy, \Nand I won't do anything to harm you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.63,0:21:50.45,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I don't need your faith or trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.00,0:21:55.41,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,For now, just understand that with your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.78,0:22:01.20,Default,Guideau,0,0,0,,Get out already.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.20,0:22:03.96,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Oh, I can't go anywhere until I heal up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.43,0:22:06.26,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,I have broken bones, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.73,0:22:10.78,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Oh, that smarts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.19,0:22:14.30,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Dear me, what a mess you've made.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.12,0:22:19.60,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,This takes me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.54,0:22:25.66,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,To three years ago, when we first met.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.98,0:24:05.16,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Lady Witch, would you return \Nto the Order with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.97,0:24:09.92,Default,Ashaf,0,0,0,,Next time: "Eloquence \Nand Silence: Opening Act."
